{
  "texts": [
    "They are necessarily vague and need to be put into practice [107,151,180].",
    "An ethics board could interpret principles in the abstract (e.g., defining terms or clarifying the purpose of specific principles) or in concrete cases (e.g.",
    "whether a research project violates a specific principle).",
    "6 The board could also be responsible for reviewing and updating principles (e.g.",
    "to also acknowledge the impact of AI on animals [159])."
